commit.message:
scanner: no longer dump debug messages to stderr

When varlink_object_new_from_json is fuzzed it receives a lot of bogus
json strings and clutters stderr with messages like "2 != 4" instead of
just returning errors. Given that it's the only place where fprintf is
used like that it seems it was left there accidentally and can
probably be safely removed to make the API more consistent in general.

It should make it easier to fuzz the library and other than that it
should also make it possible to compile libvarlink on some architectures
without compiler warnings like
```
../lib/scanner.c:628:49: warning: format specifies type 'long' but the argument has type 'size_t' (aka 'unsigned int') [-Wformat]
                fprintf(stderr, "%ld != %ld\n", utf8_len, size);
                                 ~~~            ^~~~~~~~
                                 %zu
../lib/scanner.c:628:59: warning: format specifies type 'long' but the argument has type 'size_t' (aka 'unsigned int') [-Wformat]
                fprintf(stderr, "%ld != %ld\n", utf8_len, size);
                                        ~~~               ^~~~
                                        %zu
```
array: zero-initialize newly allocated array memory

fix: avoid use-after-free after varlink_call_unref()

The code accessed "call->connection" after "call" has been freed by
varlink_call_unref().

Refactor this pattern and make a save a pointer to connection before
freeing call.
tests: prevent memory leak in test-json

fix: prevent memory leak in object_add_field()

On errors the Field has to be freed with field_freep to also free the
allocated name member.

Fixes #51

Optimize message generation in object.c.

Avoid using printf-like functions when not necessary; this avoids
scanning the string before writing it.

Can be done for more files as well. To minimize the diff and logic
differences, using only fputs instead of a combination of fputc and
fputs might make sense.

feat: Allow uppercase letters in interface names

Signed-off-by: Harald Hoyer <harald@hoyer.xyz>
fix: free stream->in if allocating stream->out fails
fix: use sizeof buf instead of hardcoding read size
fix: correct typo in error message of test-symbols

fix: use readelf with `--lto-syms` in case of LTO

In case LTO was activated, the gnu linker places the symbols in
.gnu.lto sections, which `readelf` prior to `2.36.1` did not understand.
Later versions support the `--lto-syms` option, which is now used for
the `test-symbols` test case.

Fixes: https://github.com/varlink/libvarlink/issues/30
version 22
tests: clean up test suite

fix: pay attention to ERANGE from strtod_l()

Check for errno ERANGE from strtod_l().

fix: recognize ERANGE error from strtol()

Previously very big and very negative integer values were parsed as
LONG_MIN or LONG_MAX, because errno ERANGE of strtol was not payed
attention to.

fix: verify for correct utf-8 strings

Also disallow escaped_null_in_key and string_null_escape.
Also disallow unescaped tabs and newlines in strings.
ci: declare structure_500_nested_arrays as accepted

fix: limit the array/object depth to 1000

This avoids a stack overflow, due to quasi recursive function calls.

fix: fail for ending with UTF8 surrogate

https://labs.bishopfox.com/tech-blog/an-exploration-of-json-interoperability-vulnerabilities
fix: correct main signature of lib/test-object.c

tests: move failing tests to test/FAILS and test/SEGFAULTS

A fixed test in `test/FAILS` should be moved back to `test`.

Also convert the json tests to meson native tests.
tests: add JSONTestSuite
ci: .packit.yaml update

tests: add glibc-langpack-de to spec file

glibc-langpack-de needs to be installed during rpm build for the test
suite.
ci: add .packit.yaml
version 21

fix: use strtod_l

Generate the C LC_NUMERIC once and use it for all strtod_l in the
parser.
fix: return VARLINK_ERROR_PANIC on float Inf or NaN

tests: add test with de_DE.UTF-8 locale

de_DE.UTF-8 uses `,` as the radix character. Check if json parsing and
writing switches to the C LC_NUMERIC.
ci: install de_DE.UTF-8 locale
